2026-02-08T14:31:21: {"level":30,"time":1770582681304,"pid":81390,"hostname":"err-Stealth-16-AI-Studio-A1VGG","reqId":"req-1e","targetUrl":"http://127.0.0.1:3001/mcp","method":"POST","contentType":"application/json","body":"{\"method\":\"tools/call\",\"params\":{\"_meta\":{\"openai/userAgent\":\"Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Ubuntu; Linux x86_64; rv:147.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/147.0\",\"openai/locale\":\"en-US\",\"openai/userLocation\":{\"city\":\"Phoenix\",\"region\":\"Arizona\",\"country\":\"US\",\"timezone\":\"America/Phoenix\",\"latitude\":\"33.44838\",\"longitude\":\"-112.07404\"},\"timezone_offset_minutes\":360,\"openai/subject\":\"v1/EoL8uJNwuHvN3hSuCC9BvtYvBPjCdVdLp6PTYPGDOQt8z4LENEQfcU\",\"openai/session\":\"v1/4qFqj35bJpD44kMwoHzx2cDg1iCypjDQm7UMcmIwhqf35NpiWC84jOc91X8zcbIwRfpkNuEilULl\"},\"name\":\"apply_patch\",\"arguments\":{\"diff\":\"*** Begin Patch\\n*** Add File: spec/2026-02-08-opencode-delegation-tools.md\\n+# OpenCode Delegation Without Raw REST\\n+\\n+Date: 2026-02-08\\n+\\n+## Problem\\n+\\n+The current MCP surface in `services/mcp-fs-oauth` exposes **low-level REST passthrough tools**:\\n+\\n+- `opencode_rest`\\n+- `openplanner_rest`\\n+- `workspace_rest`\\n+\\n+and a few partial wrappers (`list_agents`, `list_sessions`, `opencode_session_*`, `workspace_*`).\\n+\\n+This forces the user (and the assistant) to:\\n+\\n+1) understand undocumented API routes (`/session/{id}/prompt_async`, message listing paths, etc.),\\n+2) infer task state from raw message history,\\n+3) debug base URL mismatches (HTML shell instead of JSON),\\n+4) manually stitch multi-step workflows (delegate → poll → result extraction).\\n+\\n+The result is fragile delegation:\\n+\\n+- **agent mismatch/fallback** is not caught early,\\n+- sessions can finish with **no final report**,\\n+- prompt endpoints can return **HTML** when misconfigured,\\n+- confirmation dialogs show confusing intent strings because the tool surface is too generic.\\n+\\n+## Review of current REST tool implementations\\n+\\n+All REST tools share the same helper:\\n+\\n+- `callApi(baseUrl, method, apiPath, body?, apiKey?)`\\n+\\n+Key observations:\\n+\\n+### 1) No “wrong endpoint” detection\\n+\\n+`callApi` sets `Accept: application/json` but does not treat HTML as a hard error.\\n+If a base URL points at a UI origin (or proxy route), callers can receive an HTML app shell and proceed as if it were a meaningful response.\\n+\\n+### 2) No workflow contract\\n+\\n+`delegate_task`:\\n+\\n+- creates a session with `{ agent: agentType }`\\n+- posts to `prompt_async`\\n+- returns immediately\\n+\\n+There is no:\\n+\\n+- validation that `agentType` exists,\\n+- verification that the created session’s agent matches the request,\\n+- waiting/polling semantics,\\n+- result extraction.\\n+\\n+### 3) Duplicated but incomplete “wrapper” tools\\n+\\n+We already have wrappers like `opencode_session_prompt`, but they expose the same correctness hazards as `opencode_rest`:\\n+\\n+- caller must know sync vs async semantics (`prompt` vs `prompt_async`)\\n+- caller must know how to find results (message endpoints)\\n+\\n+### 4) Workspace REST wrappers are easy to misconfigure\\n+\\n+`WORKSPACE_API_BASE_URL` defaults to `/api/workspace` and wrappers call `/meta`, `/list`, `/file`.\\n+If the gateway expects `/api/workspace/workspace/*` (or vice versa), tools will 404.\\n+Because errors are returned as generic text, the assistant must reverse engineer the routing mismatch.\\n+\\n+## Goal\\n+\\n+Keep `*_rest` tools for power users, but make them **non-primary**.\\n+Provide **high-level, precise tools** that:\\n+\\n+- encode the workflow steps,\\n+- validate inputs,\\n+- return compact, structured results,\\n+- and produce stable confirmation dialogs.\\n+\\n+## Proposed tool set (replace “understand the API” with “name the intent”)\\n+\\n+### OpenCode: Delegation Workflow Tools\\n+\\n+#### `opencode_agent_list`\\n+\\n+- returns an array of agents with `{ name, mode, description? }`\\n+- no truncation by default; supports `maxResults`\\n+\\n+#### `opencode_agent_validate`\\n+\\n+- input: `{ agent: string }`\\n+- output: `{ ok: boolean, resolvedAgent?: string, reason?: string }`\\n+- if unknown, includes a short list of closest matches\\n+\\n+#### `opencode_task_create`\\n+\\n+Creates a session and submits the initial prompt.\\n+\\n+Input:\\n+\\n+```json\\n+{\\n+  \\\"agent\\\": \\\"hephaestus\\\",\\n+  \\\"title\\\": \\\"…\\\",\\n+  \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"…\\\",\\n+  \\\"requireFinalReport\\\": true,\\n+  \\\"labels\\\": [\\\"delegation\\\"]\\n+}\\n+```\\n+\\n+Output:\\n+\\n+```json\\n+{\\n+  \\\"taskId\\\": \\\"<opaque>\\\",\\n+  \\\"sessionId\\\": \\\"ses_…\\\",\\n+  \\\"requestedAgent\\\": \\\"hephaestus\\\",\\n+  \\\"actualAgent\\\": \\\"hephaestus\\\",\\n+  \\\"state\\\": \\\"queued|running\\\"\\n+}\\n+```\\n+\\n+Behavior:\\n+\\n+- validates agent exists\\n+- verifies created session agent matches\\n+- stores a `taskId → sessionId` mapping (in-memory is fine initially)\\n+\\n+#### `opencode_task_status`\\n+\\n+Input: `{ taskId | sessionId }`\\n+\\n+Output:\\n+\\n+```json\\n+{\\n+  \\\"state\\\": \\\"queued|running|completed|failed\\\",\\n+  \\\"updatedAt\\\": 123,\\n+  \\\"hasFinalReport\\\": true|false,\\n+  \\\"lastEvent\\\": \\\"…\\\"\\n+}\\n+```\\n+\\n+#### `opencode_task_wait`\\n+\\n+Input: `{ taskId | sessionId, timeoutMs?: number, pollMs?: number }`\\n+\\n+Returns once state is terminal.\\n+\\n+#### `opencode_task_result`\\n+\\n+Input: `{ taskId | sessionId, maxChars?: number }`\\n+\\n+Output:\\n+\\n+```json\\n+{\\n+  \\\"finalReport\\\": \\\"…\\\",\\n+  \\\"filesChanged\\\": [\\\"…\\\"],\\n+  \\\"notes\\\": [\\\"…\\\"],\\n+  \\\"rawSessionId\\\": \\\"ses_…\\\"\\n+}\\n+```\\n+\\n+Behavior:\\n+\\n+- pulls messages and extracts the *final assistant report* (last assistant message not marked as tool-calls)\\n+- if missing and `requireFinalReport=true`, automatically sends a “write final report now; no tools” prompt and retries\\n+\\n+#### `opencode_task_log_tail`\\n+\\n+Input: `{ taskId | sessionId, limit?: number }`\\n+\\n+Output: compact events:\\n+\\n+```text\\n+2026-02-08T… tool: fs_glob …\\n+2026-02-08T… tool: fs_read …\\n+2026-02-08T… assistant: (short)\\n+```\\n+\\n+### Workspace: Prefer fs_* Tools, Demote REST\\n+\\n+For local workspace manipulation, `fs_list/fs_glob/fs_grep/fs_read/fs_write/fs_delete` already provide a safe, predictable interface.\\n+\\n+Recommendation:\\n+\\n+- Mark `workspace_rest` as **advanced** in descriptions and docs.\\n+- Add `workspace_api_health`:\\n+  - calls `/meta` and verifies JSON content-type\\n+  - returns a specific error if HTML/404 is received, with suggested base URL forms.\\n+\\n+### OpenPlanner: Same pattern\\n+\\n+Keep `openplanner_rest` but add:\\n+\\n+- `openplanner_session_list` (already exists)\\n+- `openplanner_session_get` (new)\\n+- `openplanner_session_tail` (new)\\n+\\n+…so common usage does not require route knowledge.\\n+\\n+## Changes to `services/mcp-fs-oauth` (implementation plan)\\n+\\n+1) Add **content-type guards** in `callApi`:\\n+   - if HTML, return `ok=false` with a standardized error payload.\\n+\\n+2) Implement the `opencode_task_*` tools using existing REST calls internally.\\n+   - Keep `opencode_rest` for debugging only.\\n+\\n+3) Update README:\\n+   - steer users to `opencode_task_*` for delegation\\n+   - document which fields appear in confirmation dialogs (`intent` fields).\\n+\\n+4) Tests:\\n+   - unit tests for HTML-detection and for agent validation\\n+   - contract test that a task with `requireFinalReport=true` yields `finalReport`.\\n+\\n+## Acceptance criteria\\n+\\n+- Delegation can be performed without specifying any REST path.\\n+- If the agent name is wrong, the tool fails fast with actionable feedback.\\n+- If OpenCode returns HTML, the tool returns a clear misconfiguration error.\\n+- A completed task reliably returns a `finalReport`.\\n+\\n*** End Patch\",\"check\":false,\"backend\":\"local\"}},\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1}","headers":{"host":"err-stealth-16-ai-studio-a1vgg.tailbe888a.ts.net","user-agent":"openai-mcp/1.0.0","content-length":"7399","accept":"application/json, text/event-stream","accept-encoding":"gzip, deflate, br, zstd","authorization":"[REDACTED]","content-type":"application/json","mcp-protocol-version":"2025-06-18","mcp-session-id":"2bc8b511-db8c-4db5-94cc-7f0052225516","tailscale-funnel-request":"?1","traceparent":"00-6988f29300000000f09d772b1b93b46e-c71d470a899d75f6-00","tracestate":"dd=s:-1;p:5c3e983dc57b7993;t.dm:-3","x-datadog-parent-id":"11523074390930818702","x-datadog-sampling-priority":"-1","x-datadog-tags":"_dd.p.tid=6988f29300000000,_dd.p.dm=-3","x-datadog-trace-id":"17338145167476241518","x-forwarded-for":"52.242.245.208","x-forwarded-host":"err-stealth-16-ai-studio-a1vgg.tailbe888a.ts.net","x-forwarded-proto":"https","x-openai-session":"v1/4qFqj35bJpD44kMwoHzx2cDg1iCypjDQm7UMcmIwhqf35NpiWC84jOc91X8zcbIwRfpkNuEilULl","x-openai-subject":"v1/EoL8uJNwuHvN3hSuCC9BvtYvBPjCdVdLp6PTYPGDOQt8z4LENEQfcU"},"msg":"proxying to MCP"}
